author: TED
description: Earlier this year, we put out a call for new TED Speakers and thousands of you submitted — here’s what comes next. Over the next few months, TED’s very own Kelli Hsu will be traveling all around the world to 9 TEDx events to watch *your* TED Talks and help pick the 9 unique speakers who will be on stage at TED2026: All of Us. First stop: Chicago. Stay tuned for more of Kelli’s travels, including a forthcoming YouTube series about the whole process.
title: One speaker from each city will get the chance to speak at TED2026. Who has what it takes? #TEDTalks

author: TED
description: As AI continues to integrate into our workplaces, how do we ensure we don’t lose what makes us human? Social psychologist Heidi Grant speaks with NiCE's CX Division president Barry Cooper about why the current era of AI is misunderstood and how working with this new technology — instead of against it — can help you grow both inside and outside of your career. (This content is made possible by NiCE. It however does not necessarily reflect the views of NiCE.)
title: How AI can help you supercharge your career #TEDIntersections #Sponsored
